inn1.comm: Mills keeps it nice and straight and cramps Warner up a bit but he defends safely
once again bang in target, this is slightly further away from the middle stump and he defends again
cramps him up for room and Warner fails to cover the line properly and gets an inside edge onto his pads
nice teasing stuff from Mills, Warner's again cramped up and he gets a thick edge on to his boot
this time he gets some proper wood on it as he steers it towards point
continues over the wicket, Warner taps it in front of mid-off but cuts off any thoughts of a single as he sees the fielder charging towards the ball
swings it away from the right-hander and has Clarke lunging forward on the drive to cover

taps it softly in front of short cover and takes his chance with a single, Guptill dives and under-arms the ball towards the bowler's stumps in one motion, a direct hit would have sent Clarke back I reckon
gets behind the line to a good length ball and defends
tries to swipe  him across the line but he mistimes the shot and gets an inside edge to the on side
keeps it up towards the batsman's body as he fends it off to the on side
lands it short of a length and he fends off the rising delivery to mid-on
Well Warner goes for the heave ho over the bowler and misses the ball completely, Mills does well to drop the ball short
times the off side punch crisply but Guptill's alert at short cover to slide and intercept it
hits a good length around middle and off and he defends

all too easy for Dan the Man, Warner tries to go over the top but fails to get under a pitched-up delivery on the off stump, the ball travels off the splice of the bat and Vettori takes the skier very easily at mid-off, a colleague of mine described the shot perfectly - a beach cricket slog
lands it on a good length on off and middle and he defends
shoulders arms to a delivery which moves away from him from the off stump
lands it on a good length around the offstump, he defends again
gets this one to come back in towards the middle stump and the batsman defends solidly
shuffles and tucks it towards square leg and tells his partner to stay back at his crease
that's a nice looking slice, he gets his backlift down and nicely angles it away to bisect the gap between backward point and cover
strays on the pads and he works it away with the movement down to fine leg
bowls a nice outswinging yorker and he defends it away
pushed towards point for a single
lands it on a good length on the off stump and he shoulders arms
Mills gets good away movement and Clarke thrusts his front pad forward and shoulders arms again
lands it on a full length outside off, he shoulders arms again
gets behind the line to a good length ball and defends
drops it slightly short of a length and he gets behind the line and defends
angles it further away from the offstump and he defends with an angled bat to the off side
well has has a jab at that outside the offstump without moving his feet and he misses it completely
Haddin still can't break free, he taps this one to the off side
a little risky but he lives to fight another day, he shapes to pull him over midwicket but he checks his shot and gets enough elevation to clear mid-on's head
opens the face of the bat ans steers it to the off side
gets nicely behind the line and drives crisply towards mid-off and takes a chance with the single, the fielder has a shy at the stumps
drops it short of a length and he defends
gets a half prod forward and punches him to the off side, the fielder at short cover gets a finger to it and saves a single
he takes a pace forward and tries to drive but Mills drops it a fraction short and beats him
angles it further away from the offstump and Clarke follows the movement as he cuts it to square third man
bowls it on a good length on the offstump and he defends
angles it towards the body and the ball clips his hip and rolls to the on side
Southee overpitches on the off stump and Haddin has a free swing of the arms, he gets to the pitch of the ball and crashes it past mid-off
full on middle and off and he defends forward
drops it short and he pulls but mistimes it slightly, he beats midwicket
angles it outside the offstump and he slices it down to third man
Southee gives him too much width outside off, Clarke bends his knee slightly, meets the ball on an angle and slices it wide of second slip and the ball runs to third man
keeps it on a good length on the off stump, he defends
opens the face of the bat and steers it wide of backward point
keeps it nice and straight as he defends back to the bowler
delivers from slightly wide of the crease, he shapes to drive but gets a thick inside edge on to his pads
lands it around the offstump, he gets across and taps it towards mid-off
he chases a wide delivery but safely angles it away past the diving gully fielder
drops it short and invites the pull but he ends up flat-batting it to mid-on

that's a terrific shot, Southee gets a little predictable with his short deliveries and this one sits up nicely for Clarke who picks the length early and pulls it over square leg, the ball slows down before reaching the rope
bowls it a little fuller, Clarke defends
draws him forward again and he tries to angle it wide of point
he improvises by walking across his stumps and flicking a delivery angling across him, he times it well enough to beat mid-on, Elliott gives the chase

very cheap dismissal there, Southee keeps it slightly wide of the offstump, the ball holds its line after pitching and Haddin tries to cut without really getting beside the line of the ball, he gets a tame edge to McCullum, he tried to steer it down to third man actually
gets behind the line to a good length ball and defends
keeps it on off and middle and he closes the face of the bat and clips it to midwicket
gets forward and defends to the off side
gets across his stumps and drives straight and firmly but he fails to beat the bowler
drops it a little short and on the pads and he clips it wide of short square leg
keeps it on middle and leg, he tucks it to the on side
steers it wide of slip and down to third man and Mills does well to run across and cut it off
gets behind the line and defends
angles it on the body and he works it with the movement to deep square-leg
full on the offstump and he drives to cover
lands it full on middle and off and he drives firmly to the covers again
angles it on the body and he shuffles and clips it to the on side
flighted on the off stump, defended back to the bowler
pushes it quicker, he quickly gets across and defends
takes a couple of paces down the track and checks his shot as he defends
gives him the charge again and he gets to the pitch of the ball and clips it wide of mid-on
drops it really short and cuts back on the pace, Clarke waits on it, gets in position to thwack it past extra cover, the power in the shot was enormous given the pace at which the ball was delivered
gets behind the line and defends
pushes it towards mid-on and the non-striker's sent back
times it well as he works it through the line past mid-on
keeps it on a good length outside off and he taps it to point
keeps it a fraction short and he steers it to the off side
stays back at the crease, turns the face of the bat slightly and defends
steers it towards gully
gets to the pitch of the ball and drives to mid-off
gets forward and drives back to the bowler
gets forward to drive and gets a thin inside edge on to his pads and Vettori appeals, good decision by Bucknor
gets back and punches it to the off side
lands it on a good length on the off stump and he gets a half stride forward before pushing it to the off side
a fraction fuller and he pushes it to the off side as well
he overpitches on middle and off, Clarke times the forward drive very crisply and the ball beats the bowler in a flash and mid-on who dives in vain
steers a good length ball to the off side
clips it very firmly towards mid-on, that looked like four the moment it left the bat
turns the face of the bat to clip it away to the on side but he fails to beat mid-on
slow through the air on the off stump and he defends
full on middle and off and driven to mid-off
chips down the track and works it against the turn to long-on
turns just a bit, he checks his shot and defends
flighted on middle and off and worked against the turn to the on side
flighted on middle and off and he checks his shot again and taps it safely
gets width outside off and he cuts hard but the fielder at backward point does well to fall ton his right and cut it off
full on the offstump and driven very firmly to short cover
gets forward and taps it wide of short cover this time
a little slower, Hussey continues to prod forward and target the gap at cover

direct hit and David Hussey's got to go! He pushes a good length ball in front of mid-off and takes a chance with a sharp single to Vettori, unfortunately he taps it to Vettori's left and that enables him to gather the ball quickly and fire it on the stumps with his throwing arm, the third umpire takes a look and Hussey's just short of the crease
slower ball on the offstump, he defends to the off side
comes over the wicket to the left-hander, he overpitches outside the offstump and a mere defensive push on the front foot is enough to beat mid-off, nice way to get off the mark
lands outside off and he defends to the off side
sprays it on the pads, he clips it with the turn to square leg
drops it a fraction short on the offstump, he rocks back, waits for the turn and cuts
thrusts his pad forward and shoulders arms
quicker through the air, he gets forward early and defends
full on the offstump, he gets behind the line and drives to the off side
commits to the front foot and pushes it wide of cover and sets off
Hussey's solid on the forward defense, he's looking quite comfortable at the crease
strays on the pads and he clips it just wide of McCullum
gets forward and defends back to the bowler on the walk
lands it outside off and Hussey opts to let that one go
flighted on middle and leg and driven to mid-on
flighted in the same region, he turns the face of the bat and works it to square leg
stays on the backfoot and defends a delivery which doesn't turn
flighted on middle and leg and he defends the quicker delivery
flighted on the offstump, he defends again
commits to the front foot and defends
no slip in place, the ball turns in slightly, he defends forward
slower through the air, he gets forward early and defends
shapes to defend but the bat turns a bit while making contact with the ball
poor delivery, he strays down the legside and he clips it with the turn down to fine leg, the fielder is square
pitches this on middle and off, he defends forward
drops it slightly shorter in length, he rocks back, makes room and cuts but fails to beat gully
commits early to the drive and pushes it with the turn to long-on
drops it short, the ball doesnt turn much and Clarke rocks back and cuts wide of point and cover
thrusts his front foot across and pads it away
steps forward and pushes it wide of mid-on
gets forward and defends
drives firmly but straight to Hussey, Hussey owes Clarke a single sometime, if not a beer
drives hard to the onside and Guptill does  well to slide and cut it off
lunges forward and defends
floats it on the pads and he clips it against the turn to the on side
takes a couple of paces down and checks his shot
flighted on the pads and clipped to the on side
Hussey waits for the ball and then decides to shoulder arms, he wasn't quite sure what to do
defends to the off side
he bowls a half volley outside off and Hussey follows the line and drives crisply past cover, two fielders give the chase but the ball wins
defends on the front foot
defends softly on the front foot
drops it way too short and Clarke rocks back and slaps it down to deep cover
strays on the pads, he clips it with the turn to square leg
chips down and works it to the on side
gets forward and drives to the covers
steps down the track and drives a full delivery to long-off and that's Clarke's fifty
lovely delivery, beats him as he gets forward and just drags his foot backl before the keeper whips off the bails
full on the offstump and defended to the covers
flighted on the offstump and defended to the off side
floated on the pads, he shuffles and clips it to the on side
chips down the track and works it to long-on
flighted on off and middle and defended
gets to the pitch of the ball and works it past the bowler
Hussey goes over the top, he stays at the crease, gets under a flighted delivery and slogs him over midwicket, one bounce and four
gets well forward and defends
commits to the front foot and defends to the off side
flighted on middle and leg, he clips it against the turn to the on side
starts off with a short ball, Hussey swivels and pulls but fails to time it very well, e places it well though past mid-on and midwicket
lands it on a good length on middle and leg, he defends down the track
lands it on a good length on middle and leg and the taps it down to midwicket
gets forward and pushes it to Mills at mid-off and risks a single, luckily the throw is wide of the stumps
full outside off and driven to short cover
Clarke comes down to take the ball on the full and drives towards wide mid-off
slightly flatter and shorter, Hussey goes back and pulls towards deep square leg
pushed gently towards the off side
played gently off the back foot towards cover
Hussey goes back and turns the ball off his pads behind square
defended back to the bowler on the front foot
short of a length outside off stump, Hussey swishes but misses
good length on off stump, slightly slower as well, Hussey drops it with soft hands towards the off side
good length just outside off stump at 133kmh, Clarke fends but gets beaten
too straight this time and Clarke capitalises, he moves across and flicks the ball off the pads towards the fine leg boundary, Southee holds his head in dismay, he knows that was a poor ball
played down to third man for a single
good length and line from Southee, wicket to wicket this time, Hussey defends on the front foot
Clarke pushes the ball down the ground towards long-on for a single
slower ball, played back to the bowler on the front foot
full and wide outside off, he leans forward and drives wide of extra cover
full and wide outside off and he drives on the up just wide of Taylor at extra cover, Patel sprints from long-off and does well to cut it off
full outside off and defended back to the bowler
full on the offstump and defended back to the bowler
good length on the offstump and defended towards point
hits a good length outside off, he taps it to cover
lands it full on the pads and he clips it to the onside
gives him width outside the offstump, he rocks back and cuts to backward point
keeps it around the offstump and he bends his knee slightly and square drives it to point
continues round the wicket, he bowls it full and he defends
gives him more width and he opens the face of the bat and steers it to third man
Elliott seems happy giving both of them width, he lunges forward and pushes it wide of cover
opens the face of the bat and steers it down to third man
stays back at the crease and punches hard to extra cover
pats it down to the off side
comes over the wicket, lands it on middle and leg and he clips it to the on side
the slower ball, well bowled, Clarke reads it well and digs it out
full on the pads and worked to the on side
poor delivery, Mills bowls the slower ball but digs it too short, Hussey picks the pace well and pulls firmly past square leg
he bowls a low full toss on the offstump and he pushes it to the off side
starts off with a full delivery outside off, he gets to the pitch of the ball and pushes it to mid-off
overpitched outside off, he drives firmly and pats it down to the covers
holds the length back outside off, he pushes it to the off side
gets on the backfoot and steers it towards point
pushes a full delivery to cover and sets off fast, there's a direct hit at the bowler's end but he jut makes it
plays all around it to the off side very close to the pads and O'Brien appeals thinking it hit the pad first
this one kicks up towards his waist and he taps it softly to cover point
bowls the fuller ball on the off stump and he digs it out behind square on the off side
opens the face of the bat and glides a slower ball to short third man who slides and cuts it off, Hussey thinks it's four for the taking but he settles for a single
full on the offstump and he pushes it to the off side
Hussey tries to club it away but he fails to pick the slower one this time, the ball hits his body and stops in front of the stumps, Clarke sets off for the run and Hussey complies
lovely shot, he bowls a low full toss on the pads, he shuffles and clips it away with ease past square leg
pushes it to the off side and sets off for a quick single, O'Brien has a shy at the stumps but Hussey's home and that's his fifty
goes for a wild swing and a miss outside off and misses
bowls it full outside off and he digs it out to the off side
another full delivery almost jammed in on a yorker length, he digs it out to mid-off
Southee returns and starts off with a inswinging yorker which Clarke digs out well
full on middle and leg and pushed to long-on
bowls a half volley outside off and pushed to deep cover, the throw is just a little late but the batsman's home
full outside the offstump and pushed down to long-off
lands it outside off, he waits for the turn before cutting to third man
shuffles at the crease, waits for the turn before clipping it to midwicket
lands outside off and he cuts to the off side
drops it short, he swivels and shapes to slap it past square leg but he keeps it along the ground
quicker through the air, he defends to the off side
floated on the pads and clipped to fine leg
lands outside off and he reverse sweeps to short third man
gives him the charge but changes his mind and drives to mid-off instead
picks it from outside off, gets on his knee and sweeps to deep square leg
slower through the air, he waits for the turn and tucks it to midwicket
lands it outside off, he rocks back and cuts to deep point
bowls it flat and quick, he covers the line quickly and taps it back to the bowler
lands it outside off, he waits for the turn and then cuts
he stays on the front foot and pulls and short delivery safely past square leg
he too shapes to play a front foot pull, he mishits the ball but it falls on the vacanr spaces at mid-on
drives a full delivery straight to long-off
not quite short enough to pull but he goes through with the shot anyway and places it to deep square leg
full on off and driven to cover
lands outside off, he stays at the crease and cuts to point
angles the arm ball in towards middle, he makes room and cuts to the off side
flatter through the air, he gets forward and pushes it to the covers
slower through the air and he taps it past cover
steps down the track and then checks his stroke, he clips it straight to midwicket
oh a swing and a miss, rare false shot by Clarke, he tries to slog Vettori but the ball straightens
drops it short, he swivels and pulls to deep square leg
lands it outside off and gets a bit of turn, he defends to the off side
makes room, waits for the turn and slaps it to sweeper cover
he clips it down towards deep midwicket and an enthusiastic Guptill charges forward but over-runs the ball, that allows an extra run
cut to backward point, he goes so far back at the crease that his backfoot nearly trods on to the stumps
stays on the backfoot and cuts wide of backward point
slower on the pads and he works it away easily down to Fulton at deep square-leg
aims for the yorker outside off and he makes room and drives hard to long-on, the throw is flat and quick and Southee fails to deflect it back to the stumps

taps it towards Taylor at short mid-off and sends his partner back, Taylor relays the throw to the bowler wide of the stumps but the batsman makes it home and collides with Taylor in the process and tumbles
makes room to carve it away but he;s beaten for pace and movement
full on the offstump and pushed to long-off
nice shot, Southee bowls the slower one and drops it too short, Clarke makes room and slaps it past extra cover, full marks for placement as the ball beats deep cover
slower ball outside the off stump, he opens the face and steers it to the off side
nudges it to deep square leg and pushes the second run, Hussey is struggling a bit and dives at the crease, O Brien whips off the bails but Hussey's just home
goes for a wild swing across the line and places it to midwicket
chips down the track and places it to long-off

simply awesome work by Guptill! Hussey slogs O'Brien down to long-on, Guptill pedals backwards towards the boundary, takes the catch, the momentum pushes him towards the rope and he has the presence of mind to release the ball, he saved six runs there, legen - (wait for it) - dary!
the slower ball consumes him this time, he goes for a wild flat batted slog but mistimes it completely, Vettori takes it easily at midwicket running backwards slightly
pushed back to the bowler
full on the pads and he works it away to deep square leg, two fielders give the chase and one of them just pulls it back before the rope
fires in the yorker and he digs it out just in front of the stumps and sets off
full outside off and driven to sweeper cover
walks across his stumps and works a low full toss wide of midwicket
walks across his stumps again and pushes a full delivery to long-off
bowls a fairly high away swinging full toss and he taps it away to the covers

that's a toe crusher, and ouch that hurts! He takes a single to midwicket and he calls for assistance, the physio comes out and Clarke's called for a bye runner, surely Iain O'Brien's going to blog about this tonight, well actually he decides against the bye runner
makes a lot of room and plays out an inswinging yorker to the on side

and Clarke misses out on a century! O'Brien bowls an inswinging yorker down the leg side, Clarke steps down the track and tries to clip it wide of midwicket, the ball hits his pad and deflects on to the stumps
he slides down the leg side but it's way too wide and he can;t get wood on it, McCullum fumbles
gets underneath a full delivery and scoops it down to deep midwicket
full on middle and off and he turns the face of the bat and gets off the mark in international cricket with a clip to midwicket
full on the off stump and driven to long-off
slides wide down the leg side and he tries to flick it away with his pad
makes a lot of room and digs out a low full toss to long-off
gets another yorker and he digs it out to the off side again
tries to get under a yorker but he has to settle for another single to long-off
bowls another slower one and Ferguson is firced to check his shot and clip it down to deep midwicket
angles a low full toss on middle and leg, he tucks it down to deep midwicket, just seven off that over, nice stuff from Mills
bowls a slower ball around the off stump and he stays at the crease and scoops it towards long-off
bowls a low full  toss on the pads and he clips it away down to deep square leg
full outside off and driven firmly through the line to long-off
digs the slower ball much shorter, he swivels and pulls, the top edge is skied for a long time but it's too much for short fine leg to run back and take the catch
gets forward and pushes it to long-on
a high full toss hovering around the waist, he pushes it hard down to long-off

inn2.comm: good length on middle and leg, defended off the front foot back to the bowler
short of a length on middle and off, defended watchfully on the off side
straying on the pads, he tries to turn it down fine, gets a leg bye as it clips his pads
short of a length outside off, waits for it and opens the face to guide it to point
short of a good length on middle and leg, defended towards midwicket
short of a good length on the off stump, defended on the front foot to cover
shaping away from the right hander, bowled on a good length outside off, McCullum opens the face to guide it to third man
good movement away from the batsman, fuller outside off, Guptill lets it go
bang on target, a testing line just marginally outside off, there's some late movement away as well, defended solidly on the off side
held it back a touch this time, in the channel outside off, left alone
beaten! Short of a good length outside off, hitting the pitch hard and then swinging away, Guptill prods at it away from his body, is done in by the movement and the extra bounce
much straighter and plays it well this time, gets forward and defends it confidently towards mid-off
pitched outside leg and struck him on the pads as he tried to work it away fine
down the leg side, McCullum fails to glance it down fine, given a wide anyway
full on middle and moving into the right hander, driven firmly to mid-on
almost! Short of a length on the off, spat off the pitch but McCullum played it with soft hands, it took the outside edge and fell short of a diving Cameron White at slip
short on middle and leg, pushed away into the leg side towards square leg for a couple
full on the pads, shuffles just a touch and flicks it away wide of short fine for two more
good length on middle and leg, pushed off the front foot to mid-on
fielded well off his own bowling, driven firmly back to him, he sticks out his left hand to prevent a couple of runs
dropped short of cover for a quick single
full outside off, and in the zone for McCullum, he makes a bit of room and carts it over the covers for a boundary
misdirected slower ball bowled short outside leg stump, he tries to help it on its way to the fine-leg boundary, misses, but it's given a wide

dropped, short and wide, Guptill cuts it away powerfully over Clarke at point, the ball clips Michale Clarke's fingers on its way to the boundary. He was slow to react there, perhaps still recovering from the sore toe
shot! Fractionally short outside off and Guptill eases that through the covers off the back foot fot three runs
almost chopped it on, short of a length on the off stump, not enough room there to cut, he tries to do just that, gets an inside edge that doesn't miss the off stump by much
beaten! Short of a good length outside off, anging away with the angle, he tries to defend it off the back foot, misses

he's gone finally, Clarke will be mightily relieved, much fuller outside off and he attempts a rather lethargic drive with minimum foot movement, gets an outside edge and White snaps a good low catch at first slip
full on middle and leg, driven wide of midwicket off the front foot for a couple
held its line this time, good length outside off, he gets outside the line to defend it back to the bowler
pitched outside leg and moved into Fulton who tried to work that away on the leg side, got an inside edge onto his pads
a good testing line outside off stump, going away with the angle, Fulton shoulders arms to that one
short on middle and leg, turned away off his hips towards square leg

short on middle, McCullum senses a chance and goes for a mighty pull over square leg, the ball brushes his trousers on the way to the keeper. Haddin goes up, so does the bowler, but the umpire Paul Reiffel is unmoved
short of a length on middle and leg, played away to square leg
bouncer banged in short on middle, McCullum ducks under it, one for the over
short of a good length on leg stump, tries to turn it away fine, is struck on the thighs
similar ball, similar result, the ball drops on the leg side, they decide against the single
good length outside off, pushed firmly off the front foot wide of mid-off for a single
full outside off, opens the face to run it down to third man
pitching on a good length on middle and off, defended off the front foot to the bowler
fuller on the off stump, lunges forward to push it to cover
short of a length on the off stump, defended off the back foot to cover
good length outside off, left alone to the keeper
straying in line this time, its full on the pads, flicked away through square leg for three runs
on a good length on middle and leg, driven off the front foot to mid-on
pushed off the front foot wide of a diving cover, Clarke gives chase but returns a rather wayward throw to the non-strikers end, the batsmen run an easy two
ouch! Short on middle, Fulton attempts to duck, it hits him on his back, but he's fine, no show of pain there

missed run out, short of a length on middle, turned away to midwicket and McCullum is halfway down the pitch, the fielder takes aim but misses the stumps at the non-strikers end by a whisker. McCullum was miles outside the crease
on middle and leg, played away to square leg
back of a length on the off stump, struck firmly to cover
he needs to bowl much fuller here it's short again outside the off stump, guided to point off the back foot
cramped him for room there, opens the face to play it to point once again
shot! Good length outside off, edges it deliberately just at the last moment wide of a diving third man for a boundary
in the channel outside off, defended into the off side
beaten this time, angling away from the right hander after it's bowled wide the crease, McCullum walks across and tries to run it down to third man, fails to make contact
poor ball and gets the treatment, full on middle and leg, Fulton gets under it and flicks it away over midwicket
held it back, its short of a length on the off stump, defended off the back foot towards cover
punched off the back foot towards point, bowled on a good length this time
begging to be hit there, banged in short on middle, its a rank long hop and Fulton rocks onto the back foot to pull it away over square leg
short of a good length on middle, defended back to the bowler
tries to cut it away towards point this time, gets a thick inside edge towards midwicket instead

Almost produces a wicket, slower ball bowled full outside off, McCullum chases it, ends up slicing it really high but in a safe zone between third man and deep cover, failed to pick the slower one there
zipped away off the pitch, short of a good length outside off and cut away as McCullum tried to defend it off the back foot
short of a length on middle and off, guided off the back foot to point
full outside off, driven firmly but straight to mid-off, who's on the circle, and they manage to sneak a single
short on middle and leg, turned away off the back foot wide of square leg for a single
pushed through the covers off the back foot for a single
tossed up on middle and off, driven back to the bowler
drifting into the batsman, tries to drive it back past Clarke, gets an inside edge towards short fine
full on middle and leg, driven to mid-on for a single
flighted on middle and leg, angling into the batsman from round the wicket, gets forward and defends
full on the pads, angling down leg, tries to work it away, is hit on the pads
shorter on middle and leg, flicked away wide of square leg for a single
slower ball bowled on a good length outside off, square driven to deep cover for a single
on middle and leg, pushed off the front foot to mid-on
short of a good length outside off, goes for it, its a touch too wide, but he fails to reach
gets forward and pushes it firmly wide of mid-off for a single
short of a good length on middle and off, defended off the back foot to the bowler
pushed off the back foot to deep cover for an easy single
tossed up on middle and leg, pushed wide of midwicket for a single
flighted on middle, tries to driven it to long-off, gets an inside edge onto his pads
